# Rock Paper Scissors Game

This is a simple implementation of the classic Rock Paper Scissors game using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

## How to Play

1. Open the `index.html` file in your web browser.
2. You will see three buttons representing Rock, Paper, and Scissors.
3. Click on one of the buttons to make your choice.
4. The computer will randomly select its choice.
5. The result of the game (win, lose, or tie) will be displayed on the screen.
6. The scores for the player and the computer will be updated accordingly.

## Game Rules

- Rock beats Scissors
- Paper beats Rock
- Scissors beat Paper
- If both players choose the same option, it's a tie.

## Project Structure

- `index.html`: The main HTML file that contains the structure of the game.
- `style.css`: The CSS file that styles the game elements.
- `script.js`: The JavaScript file that contains the game logic.

